{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing mandatory information element in PUCCH configuration\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_max_code_rate` function in the NR MAC layer was using an undefined enum type `NR_PUCCH_MaxCodeRate_t` instead of the correct `PUCCH_MaxCodeRate_t`. This caused issues with PUCCH format 2 and 3 resource allocation where the max code rate parameter couldn't be properly decoded from RRC configuration.\n\nThis fix updates the function signature and implementation to use the correct enum type that's actually defined in the codebase, ensuring proper mapping of maxCodeRate values from RRC PUCCH-Config to MAC layer processing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.c`: Updated `get_max_code_rate` function parameter type and enum value references\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_COMMON/nr_mac_common.h`: Updated function prototype and added required header include\n- Fixed enum type mismatch in `compute_pucch_prb_size` function signature\n\n"
}